HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 334
BY REPRESENTATIVE RISER
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Susan Ann Traylor Bittick
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Susan Ann
3 Traylor Bittick and to celebrate a remarkable woman whose brilliance, spirit, and
4 unforgettable presence left a lasting mark on all who knew her.
5 WHEREAS, Susan was born on September 4, 1954, in Hughes Springs, Texas, to
6 Robert "Bob" H. Traylor and Jodie Bess Wallace Traylor and was the cherished sister of
7 Gary Traylor; and
8 WHEREAS, from her earliest years, Susan was known for her vibrant spirit, warmth,
9 and ability to bring joy to those around her, qualities that remained hallmarks of her life; and
10 WHEREAS, Susan graduated from Gilmer High School in 1973 and undertook a
11 successful journalism career that spanned sixteen years, during which she served as food
12 editor for the Longview Morning Journal and city editor of the Shreveport Times; and
13 WHEREAS, Susan's sharp intellect and commanding presence earned her the
14 opportunity to cover the gubernatorial campaign of former Florida Governor Bob Martinez,
15 and she later served as his press secretary; and
16 WHEREAS, Susan relished the opportunity to challenge herself and returned to
17 school to pursue higher education; she earned a bachelor's degree in Latin American Studies
18 from Louisiana Tech University in 1990 and went on to attend St. Louis University School
19 of Law, where she distinguished herself as editor of the Law Journal and graduated in 1995;
20 and
