1 WHEREAS, in 2006, Susan earned a master of laws degree from the University of
2 Houston, which further cemented her reputation as a formidable legal and policy mind; and
3 WHEREAS, Susan devoted the last nineteen years of her accomplished career to
4 Ryan, LLC, where she most recently served as a principal in the company's U.S. advocacy
5 practice and earned national recognition as a leading and influential voice in state tax policy;
6 and
7 WHEREAS, Susan was admired by her colleagues and peers for her intellect,
8 professionalism, integrity, mentorship, extraordinary work ethic, and unwavering
9 commitment to public service; she is remembered as a dynamic, insightful, and powerful
10 advocate and described as "wicked smart," "a firecracker," and "a force to be reckoned
11 with"; and
12 WHEREAS, Susan was a cherished member of the Louisiana Capitol team,
13 affectionately known as "The Roses and The Thorns", where her wit, intuition, friendship,
14 unmistakable personality, and infectious laugh made her deeply admired and treasured
15 among the group and by all those around her; and
16 WHEREAS, despite her many professional accomplishments, Susan's greatest joy
17 was the life she built with her beloved husband, Tom Bittick, whom she met at a Christmas
18 party in 1990 and married on October 5, 1991; and
19 WHEREAS, Susan and Tom shared a passion for travel, exceptional food, fine wine,
20 and new adventures, and she was especially fond of her travels to London and countless
21 other cities around the world; and
22 WHEREAS, Susan embraced life with unmistakable style and enthusiasm, never
23 missed an opportunity to dance, and was rarely seen without her signature heels; and
24 WHEREAS, Susan was an avid reader, an accomplished gardener known for
25 producing an abundance of tomatoes and countless jars of homemade marinara sauce, an
26 avid art collector with exceptional taste and appreciation for fine art, and a devoted lover of
27 Christmas music on vinyl; she also cherished her beloved dogs, especially her rescue dog,
28 Mavis; and
