1 WHEREAS, Susan's family game nights were legendary occasions; she often insisted
2 upon playing Monopoly as the Scottie Dog token and threatened to read the entire rulebook
3 aloud whenever she suspected cheating; and
4 WHEREAS, Susan possessed a rare combination of fierce determination, quick wit,
5 immense kindness, and boundless generosity, and these qualities endeared her to family,
6 friends, colleagues, and all fortunate enough to cross her path; and
7 WHEREAS, Susan embraced Louisiana's unique culture and traditions, especially
8 enjoying annual gatherings and outdoor excursions with dear friends and colleagues that
9 celebrated the state's rich cuisine, camaraderie, and sporting heritage, particularly her
10 memorable alligator hunting adventures and her plans to transform treasured keepsakes from
11 those experiences into handcrafted items reflecting her adventurous spirit, creativity, and
12 deep love for Louisiana; and
13 WHEREAS, Susan leaves behind a legacy of love, wisdom, and devotion to her
14 family, friends, and colleagues; she is survived by her loving husband of thirty-four years,
15 Tom Bittick; her brother, Gary Traylor (Chasha); her sisters-in-law, Elizabeth Bittick Dailey
16 and Mary Bittick Camden (Mike); her uncle, Jerry Traylor; and a host of loving nieces,
17 nephews, great-nieces, and great-nephews who affectionately knew her as "The Greatest
18 Aunt"; and
19 WHEREAS, Susan Ann Traylor Bittick lived boldly, loved deeply, and left behind
20 a legacy of brilliance, kindness, humor, grace, and unmistakable flair that will continue to
21 inspire and uplift all who knew and loved her.
22 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
23 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Susan
24 Ann Traylor Bittick and does hereby extend sincere wishes that her family, friends,
25 colleagues, and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of her beautiful life.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to her
27 husband, Tom Bittick, and her brother, Gary Traylor.
